{"info": {"author": "Roberto Alsina", "author_email": "roberto.alsina@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# XRandRoll\n\nNone of the existing display configuration tools does what I think is \"the right thing\".\nSo I went and wrote one.\n\n## The Right Thing\n\n* Don't start from a stored config, use xrandr to read the systems' current state\n* Allow creating \"profiles\" that will get applied smartly (not there yet)\n* Generate a xrandr invocation to reflect the desired configuration\n* Allow per-monitor scaling\n* Allow arbitrary monitor positioning\n* Implement \"scale everything so all the pixels are the same size\"\n\n## To try:\n\nIf you have PySide2: `python -m xrandroll` in the folder where you cloned it.\n\n## TODO:\n\n* Implement other things\n* Forget about it forever\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/ralsina/xrandroll", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "xrandroll", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/xrandroll/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/xrandroll/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/ralsina/xrandroll"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/xrandroll/0.1.5/", "requires_dist": ["pyside2 (>5.14)"], "requires_python": ">3.6", "summary": "A powertool to configure your display", "version": "0.1.5", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>XRandRoll</h1>\n<p>None of the existing display configuration tools does what I think is \"the right thing\".\nSo I went and wrote one.</p>\n<h2>The Right Thing</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Don't start from a stored config, use xrandr to read the systems' current state</li>\n<li>Allow creating \"profiles\" that will get applied smartly (not there yet)</li>\n<li>Generate a xrandr invocation to reflect the desired configuration</li>\n<li>Allow per-monitor scaling</li>\n<li>Allow arbitrary monitor positioning</li>\n<li>Implement \"scale everything so all the pixels are the same size\"</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>To try:</h2>\n<p>If you have PySide2: <code>python -m xrandroll</code> in the folder where you cloned it.</p>\n<h2>TODO:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Implement other things</li>\n<li>Forget about it forever</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6572848, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "69304c0c9515d4c5c5137deeb04da706", "sha256": "9ee2ebf8783c2aec6a2149f0dfa8188e0de6d9a88bbf32095a0c30fc20e0afdb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "xrandroll-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "69304c0c9515d4c5c5137deeb04da706", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">3.6", "size": 8688, "upload_time": "2020-02-01T20:11:28", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-01T20:11:28.710799Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/31/dd/19eccb07a6fa8a66f87234b97308d7edddf63eec8b15f7c6b6aa88132dcd/xrandroll-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "81b8cbe00edcd1a531d88b21f65c8d69", "sha256": "d76214cf004be71292da0d8120ace8a0977eb9b2efb69c57322f121bae555ef1"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "xrandroll-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "81b8cbe00edcd1a531d88b21f65c8d69", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">3.6", "size": 8136, "upload_time": "2020-02-01T20:11:31", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-01T20:11:31.158463Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/21/68/69d8b6014da9e7cf48e70065720d0d0a5e74aa4539df08433d370db1b360/xrandroll-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "a7c9bf595321171a910612416aee324d", "sha256